properties.areaDesc: Ventura County Mountains; Los Angeles County Mountains excluding the Santa Monica Range
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 31 at 2:12PM PST until February 3 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 30 to 50 mph with gusts to 70 mph
possible. Local gusts up to 90 mph in the hills around the
Interstate 5 corridor.

* WHERE...Ventura and Los Angeles County Mountains excluding the
Santa Monica Range.

* WHEN...From Sunday afternoon through Monday morning.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down large objects such as
trees and power lines. Power outages are possible. Travel
could be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The combination of extremely strong winds
and possible snow showers near the Kern County line will cause
very hazardous driving conditions. Interstate 5 through the
Grapevine and Highway 33 through the Ventura County mountains
will be affected.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SUNDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH MONDAY MORNING
